        "id": "2005386640878190775",
        "text": "So, who do we have here? - from the farthest side of the table to the closest:\n\nUKRAINIAN SIDE (7 people):\n- Oleksandr Bevz — adviser to the Cabinet of the President at the Office of the President of Ukraine;\n- Oleksii Soboliev — Minister of Economy;\n- Andrii Hnatov — Chief of the General Staff of the Armed Forces of Ukraine;\n- Volodymyr Zelenskyy — President of Ukraine;\n- Rustem Umierov — Secretary of the National Security and Defense Council;\n- Serhii Kyslytsia — Deputy Minister of Foreign Affairs of Ukraine;\n- Olga Stefanishyna — Ambassador of Ukraine to the United States.\n\nU.S. SIDE (9 people):\n- Jared Kushner — businessman, Trump’s son-in-law, diplomatic adviser, and unofficial special envoy;\n- Steve Witkoff — Special Envoy to the Middle East and special envoy for peace missions (unofficially, special envoy to Russia);\n- Susie Wiles — White House Chief of Staff;\n- Marco Rubio — U.S. Secretary of State;\n- Donald Trump — President of the United States;\n- Pete Hegseth — United States Secretary of War;\n- Gen. Dan Caine — Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff;\n- Stephen Miller — White House Deputy Chief of Staff for Policy;\n- Josh Gruenbaum — Commissioner of the General Services Administration’s Federal Acquisition Service.",
